<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({1},{2}\right)}</m></li><li><image width="52%"  pi:generated="problems/images/7748c54c76637cd2fa5b522053d579d2.png" />
</li></ul></p><p>The form of a parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={a}{\left({x}-{h}\right)}^{{2}}+{k}</m>. Because this parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({x}-{1}\right)}^{{2}}+{2}</m>, which can be written <m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({x}-{\left({1}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({2}\right)}</m> we know the following.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{h}={1}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{k}={2}</m>. Thus the vertex is <m>\displaystyle{\left({1},{2}\right)}</m>.</p>
<p>To graph the parabola we can use the vertex and another convenient point. One convenient point is at <m>\displaystyle{x}={1}+{1}={2}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}{\left({2}-{\left({1}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({2}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={2}{\left({1}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({2}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={2}+{\left({2}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={4}</m>.</p>
<p>We use <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{4}\right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
